<div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto py-10 text-gray-800">
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold mb-4">Billing & Payment Terms</h1>
  <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 mb-6">Last updated: August 2025</p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    <span class="font-semibold">One annual invoice</span>, paid up front. You get a <span class="font-semibold">3-month trial</span>. No cards, demos, or marketing emails.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Prepay <span class="font-semibold">multi-year</span> terms in one check to shave <span class="font-semibold">30%</span> off the <span class="font-semibold">entire contract</span>. All prices are in <span class="font-semibold">USD</span>.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    You'll receive a <a href="/replicate-msa-dpa.pdf" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold">pre-signed MSA</a> via DocuSign a month in, which includes a required <span class="font-semibold">DPA</span>. If you do nothing, the emails eventually stop, and your data gets wiped.
    <span class="block mt-6 md:mt-0 md:inline">Invoices are emailed (via Stripe) with <span class="font-semibold">full remittance details</span>. Pay by <span class="font-semibold">card</span>, <span class="font-semibold">ACH</span>, or <span class="font-semibold">wire</span>. Only <span class="font-semibold">Net 30</span>.
    Here are the <a href="/replicate-w9.pdf" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold" target="_blank">W-9</a> and
    <%= link_to 'COI', '/replicate-coi.pdf', class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold", target: "_blank" %> docs.</span>
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    There is <span class="font-semibold">no metering</span> and <span class="font-semibold">no auto-renewal.</span> You get a reminder 30 days out, and must approve every renewal. Upgrade mid-term if you want more seats. Your unused balance rolls into the new contract.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-6">
    Sign whenever. Your term starts the 1st of the month <span class="font-semibold">after</span> your trial's end date. You always get 3 months free, along with any gap days. Partial terms are an option to align with budget cycles.
  </p>

  <div class="hidden md:block">
    <p class="flex flex-row items-center mb-6">
      <img src="/logo-white.jpg" class="rounded-full w-9 h-9 mr-3 border border-gray-500" />
      <a href="mailto:support@replicate.info" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-700 text-[16px] hover:underline hover:underline-offset-4 decoration-1 transition flex items-center">
        support@replicate.info
      </a>
    </p>
  </div>

<%# ---------- helpers (local to this template) ---------- %>
  <% two_year_total   = ->(p) { (p * 2 * 0.70).round(-2) }   # 30% off entire multi-year
     three_year_total = ->(p) { (p * 3 * 0.70).round(-2) }

     money    = ->(p) { number_to_currency(p, precision: 0) }
     money_k  = ->(p) { "$#{(p / 1000.0).round}k" }
     seats    = ->(n) { number_with_delimiter(n) }
  %>

  <!-- Pricing: desktop table (md+), text-left numbers -->
  <div class="hidden md:block">
    <div class="overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-gray-200 shadow-sm">
      <table class="min-w-full divide-y divide-gray-200 text-sm">
        <thead class="bg-gray-50 text-gray-700">
        <tr>
          <th class="px-5 py-3 text-left font-semibold">Team Size</th>
          <th class="px-5 py-3 text-left font-semibold">1 Year</th>
          <th class="px-5 py-3 text-left font-semibold">2 Years</th>
          <th class="px-5 py-3 text-left font-semibold">3 Years</th>
        </tr>
        </thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-100">
        <% @prices.each do |t| %>
          <% p1 = t[:price]; p2 = two_year_total.(p1); p3 = three_year_total.(p1) %>
          <tr class="hover:bg-gray-50/60">
            <td class="px-5 py-3">
              Up to <span class="font-semibold"><%= seats.(t[:seat_count]) %></span> engineers
            </td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 tabular-nums text-left"><%= money.(p1) %></td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 tabular-nums text-left"><%= money_k.(p2) %></td>
            <td class="px-5 py-3 tabular-nums text-left"><%= money_k.(p3) %></td>
          </tr>
        <% end %>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Pricing: mobile cards (sm), text-left numbers; hide on md+ -->
  <div class="md:hidden rounded-md border-2 border-neutral-200">
    <% @prices.each_with_index do |t, idx| %>
      <% p1 = t[:price]; p2 = two_year_total.(p1); p3 = three_year_total.(p1) %>
      <div class="<%= idx.zero? ? '' : 'border-t'  %> border-gray-200 p-4">
        <div class="text-sm text-gray-600">
          Up to <span class="font-semibold text-gray-900"><%= seats.(t[:seat_count]) %></span> engineers
        </div>
        <div class="mt-3 grid grid-cols-3 gap-3 text-sm">
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">1 Year</div>
            <div class="tabular-nums text-left font-semibold"><%= money.(p1) %></div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">2 Years</div>
            <div class="tabular-nums text-left font-semibold"><%= money_k.(p2) %></div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="text-xs text-gray-500">3 Years</div>
            <div class="tabular-nums text-left font-semibold"><%= money_k.(p3) %></div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    <% end %>
  </div>

  <h3 class="font-semibold mt-8 mb-1 text-lg">Insurance Coverage</h3>
  <p class="mb-6">Replicate Software, LLC maintains <a href="/replicate-coi.pdf" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold" target="_blank">$1M Errors & Omissions</a> and <a href="/replicate-coi.pdf" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold" target="_blank">$1M Cyber Liability</a> coverage.

  <p class="mb-2 font-semibold text-lg">Liability Cap</p>
  <p class="mb-6">Liability is capped at <span class="font-semibold">5x the fees</span> paid across your <span class="font-semibold">entire contract</span>, even if multi-year. This excludes <span class="font-semibold">serious misconduct</span> liability (e.g., IP infringement), which is uncapped as it should be.</p>

  <p class="mb-2 font-semibold text-lg">Refund Policy</p>
  <p class="mb-6">
    All sales are final. Think it over for a quarter, and align on why this investment matters (or doesn't).
  </p>

  <p class="font-semibold mb-2 text-lg">Sales Tax</p>
  <p class="mb-6">
    If you need to pay sales tax (e.g., VAT, GST, US state), <a href="https://stripe.com/tax" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold">Stripe Tax</a> automatically applies it to your invoice. Email exemption certificates to <a href="mailto:support@replicate.info" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline font-semibold">support@replicate.info</a> to apply them <span class="font-semibold">before</span> invoicing.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-2 font-semibold text-lg">Standard Agreements</p>
  <p class="mb-6">
    Replicate does not support <span class="font-semibold">RFPs</span>, <span class="font-semibold">redlines</span>, or <span class="font-semibold">vendor portals</span>. Standard buyer requirements are included by default. You shouldn't have to waste time negotiating for them.
  </p>

  <p class="mb-2 font-semibold text-lg">Support</p>
  <p class="mb-6">
    Email support is included for all tiers. Typical response time is 1-2 days.
  </p>


  <p class="text-gray-500 mt-8">
    <span class="md:hidden">
      <%= link_to 'Terms', '/terms', class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline", target: "_blank" %> &nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;
      <%= link_to 'Privacy', '/privacy', class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline", target: "_blank" %> &nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;
    </span>
    <span class="hidden md:inline">
      <%= link_to 'Terms of Service', '/terms', class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline", target: "_blank" %> &nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;
      <%= link_to 'Privacy Policy', '/privacy', class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline", target: "_blank" %> &nbsp;&nbsp;•&nbsp;&nbsp;
    </span>
    <%= link_to 'Security', '/security', class: "text-blue-600 hover:underline" %>
  </p>
</div>